cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper deals with cross-lingual model transfer for predicting annotations in low-resource languages, which is a common problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel neural network model and active learning heuristics, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of word embeddings, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL), making these categories possible as well.
